history.content: Its hard to say. The only way you can get in is if people drop, as the class will not expand anymore. The class is known to be difficult and therefore, more people end up dropping it compared to other classes. But yeah, no guarantees.

children.subject: I think as long as you stay on the waitlist, you have a decent shot of getting in by the 3rd week. I've heard 126, 127, and 189 have very high drop rates because people vastly underestimate the required mathematical maturity.

history.content: I just wanted to know what the likelihood of getting into 126 is because it would be good to know to plan ahead for taking another class instead if its not very likely.
history.subject: Spot 42 on the waitlist for EECS 126. Likelihood that I will be admitted off of it?
